snippet.textDisplay:
I will probably be eaten alive, but I see something, that according to my own subjective perception, start to seem like some kind of pushing the borders too far with some content. On one hand something honest is being said, which brings out honest reactions and then it's being followed up by cashing-in on that. Like this setup here with "another serious thing to announce".
I also have had mixed feelings when after seeing the "I thought about retirement" video and touching the subject of doing it for your family, wanting to have more of a regular life and trying to avoid mindless consumerism, the PC Build Video with your daughter came out, where it seemed that folk who had the most fun out of it was the audience, not her, not you, but I may be wrong. I am not criticizing nor accusing of anything, just stating that as a veteran fan, recently I'm starting to get new kind of vibes on this channel, which make feel slightly uneasy. I have witnessed some of creators I was a huge fan of just drifting away, either due to them losing touch with the reality, burning out or making too sharp of a turn to go different direction to accommodate temporary trends. I don't want "to lose Linus" too, not necessarily by the content failing in viewership, but also by it making too sharp of a turn for me to stick along.


You guys may do whatever you want with this comment, I really write it in good will :P Good luck with the LTX!
